"People are always stressed, houses are expensive, as well as education, so many people postpone it," says the young official.
"The others have children.
But it is important for me to rely on my own money and time," says another, about 20-year-old, young man.
Men and women refer to careers, stress and the cost of living and education as reasons that prevent them from having children.
